   <titles>
      <title>Intervals</title>
      <plain.title>Intervals</plain.title>
   </titles>
   <intro>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>We will frequently encounter sets of numbers which correspond to a line segment on the number line. Such a set of numbers is called an interval.</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
   </intro>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <def type="Definition" id="Def_Interval">
               <caption>Number intervals</caption>
               <associate type="Explanation">
                  <info>
                     <info.caption>Explanation</info.caption>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>Read the symbol construct</para.body>
                     </para>
                     <math.display>
                        <latex>\CCIntrvl{a}{b} := \Set{ x\in \RNr \st a\leq x\leq b}</latex>
                     </math.display>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>as: ‘the closed interval from a to b is defined to be the set of all those x in R such that a less than or equal to x less than or equal to b’.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </info>
               </associate>
               <associate type="Explanation">
                  <info>
                     <info.caption>Explanation</info.caption>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>Read the symbol construct</para.body>
                     </para>
                     <math.display>
                        <latex> \COIntrvl{a}{b} := \Set{ x\in \RNr \st a\leq x\leq b} </latex>
                     </math.display>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>as: ‘the left closed right open interval from a to b is defined to be the set of all those x in R such that a less than or equal to x less than b’.</para.body>
                     </para>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>The remaining definitions of intervals are read similarly.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </info>
               </associate>
               <def.body>
